BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: Assistance League of Austin Texas Inc

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Assistance League of Austin is a nonprofit organization of dedicated volunteers providing direct services that address specific, basic needs of children and adults in schools and hospitals in the Greater Austin area.
IRS990.MissionDesc: Assistance League volunteers transforming the lives of children and adults through community programs.
IRS990.Desc: Operation School Bell is the flagship program of Assistance League chapters providing a wardrobe of new clothing, shoes, and toiletries to children in Austin ISD, Del Valle ISD and Manor ISD schools and area shelters to boost students self esteem and help them stay in school.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Assistance League Scholarships are provided to qualifying students attending Austin Community College to help them achieve their career goals. These scholarships cover tuition, books, and fees. Discretionary funds are provided to students as needed and approved.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Toy Cart at Dell Children's Medical Center brings joy to sick and injured children by giving them a toy and a book several times a week.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part V, Line 4: Intended uses of the endowment fund.
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The ALA Endowment Fund is held and administered by Austin Community Foundation. The endowment provides unrestricted earnings to support the Organization's operations and programs.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: Comfort items for kids in hospital
GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.NonCashAssistanceDesc: A gift of a book and a toy or game

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: Clothes and comfort items for kids

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: *Austin Community College Foundation - The Organization receives financial statements each semester from ACCF for each scholar. Unused funds are rolled over and used the following semester. Comparisons are made each semester to see that the accounts are accurate.*Manor Independent School District - The Organization purchases items for each selected school and most items are delivered directly to the schools. For each delivery, the receiving employee fills out an acknowledgment form. The acknowledgment form includes the date of receipt, delivery carrier, address received, a description of items, and is signed by the school employee. Some purchases are received by the Organization and delivered to the selected school.

OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 4: Operation Wish List provides assistance to Central Texas area school districts which have a high percentage of students at risk. OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 5: Outreach is designed to address one time or short term needs in the community. OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 6: Waste Not program provides oversight for the distribution of excess and unusable items donated to (or purchased for use by) Thrift House, Operation School Bell, or other programs. Distributions are made only to other non-profit agencies. OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 7: The Organization's programs are conducted by unpaid volunteer members who provide valuable services to individuals within the community. Membership in the Organization includes membership in National Assistance League. OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 8: The Assault Survivor Kits program provides clothing, toiletries and a book on surviving assault to help restore dignity to child and adolescent survivors of assault treated at Dell Children's Medical Center Hospital.
